"{\"uid\": \"standard.co.uk-sport-sport-olympics-what-is-dsd-boxing-imane-khelif-gender-scandal-paris-olympics-2024-intersex-b1174430.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"To use the search feature, we need your consent to load Google Custom Search, which may use cookies or similar technologies.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 124, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 56, \"end\": 76, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Google Custom Search\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Please click 'Allow and Continue' below to enable search.\", \"from\": 125, \"to\": 182, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"See our privacy policy for more information.\", \"from\": 183, \"to\": 227, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sport|Olympics  Imane Khelif, the Algerian boxer at the centre of theParis Olympics'genderrow, willfight for gold after winning her semi-final.\", \"from\": 229, \"to\": 372, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 245, \"end\": 257, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"score\": 0.9999996421621021, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Imane Khelif\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\"}, {\"begin\": 263, \"end\": 271, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"score\": 0.9861573199373006, \"rank\": 0.014035996947992214, \"text\": \"Algerian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Khelif found herself in the midst of controversy last Thursday when Italian fighter Angela Cariniabandoned her boutwith Khelif less than a minute into it.\", \"from\": 374, \"to\": 528, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 442, \"end\": 449, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\", \"score\": 0.85689379349688, \"rank\": 0.16562763988918258, \"text\": \"Italian\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And on Wednesday theAlgerian booked her place in the final, having beaten Janjaem Suwannapheng of Thailandin the women's welterweight clash at Roland Garros.\", \"from\": 530, \"to\": 687, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Khelif won every round on the judges' cards, appearing close to securing a stoppage at times, and celebrated with a victory jig in the ring as the Algerian supporters celebrated wildly.\", \"from\": 689, \"to\": 874, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 836, \"end\": 844, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"score\": 0.9861573199373006, \"rank\": 0.014035996947992214, \"text\": \"Algerian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The participation of Khelif and Taiwan featherweight Lin Yu-ting has caused an international storm sinceKhelif beat Angela Carini of Italy in just 46 secondsin her opening bout.\", \"from\": 876, \"to\": 1053, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 908, \"end\": 914, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"score\": 0.9999999855363059, \"rank\": 1.1527654980638812e-08, \"text\": \"Taiwan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\"}, {\"begin\": 929, \"end\": 940, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lin Yu-ting\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\"}, {\"begin\": 1009, \"end\": 1014, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.779820787670367, \"rank\": 0.28214340411895045, \"text\": \"Italy\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Both Khelif and Lin were disqualified by the InternationalBoxingAssociation (IBA) during last year's World Championships for failing to meet gender eligibility criteria.\", \"from\": 1055, \"to\": 1224, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1132, \"end\": 1135, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9999998432986227, \"rank\": 1.567017860267551e-07, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It said at the time that the pair's \\\"elevated levels of testosterone failed to meet the eligibility criteria\\\" for the women's competition.\", \"from\": 1226, \"to\": 1364, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She has, however, been ruled eligible for the Games by theInternational Olympic Committeeand now advances into the final of of the women's 66kg tournament.\", \"from\": 1365, \"to\": 1520, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In her previous fight, which stirred up the controversy, her Italian opponent Carini broke down in tears as she pulled out of the fight, having been caught twice by powerful blows from Khelif.\", \"from\": 1522, \"to\": 1714, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1583, \"end\": 1590, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\", \"score\": 0.85689379349688, \"rank\": 0.16562763988918258, \"text\": \"Italian\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1600, \"end\": 1606, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carini\", \"score\": 0.7271917328355142, \"rank\": 0.37515314716380394, \"text\": \"Carini\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carini\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The fight attracted worldwide attention and many weighed in on the incident, leading to Khelif having to defend herself.\", \"from\": 1716, \"to\": 1836, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In an interview with SNTV on Sunday, Khelifspoke out.\", \"from\": 1838, \"to\": 1891, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I send a message to all the people of the world to uphold the Olympic principles and the Olympic Charter, to refrain from bullying all athletes, because this has effects, massive effects,\\\" she said in Arabic.\", \"from\": 1892, \"to\": 2101, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Itauma postpones Franklin fight after training injury  Aquatics GB 'immensely disappointed' as Proud joins Enhanced Games  Sports quiz of 2024: 100 hard questions on an incredible year  Reset your wellbeing for the year ahead  \\\"It can destroy people, it can kill people's thoughts, spirit and mind.\", \"from\": 2103, \"to\": 2401, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It can divide people.\", \"from\": 2402, \"to\": 2423, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And, because of that, I ask them to refrain from bullying.\\\"\", \"from\": 2424, \"to\": 2483, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After their fight, Carini explained she had never been hit so hard and decided to withdraw because of the intense pain in her nose.\", \"from\": 2485, \"to\": 2616, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2504, \"end\": 2510, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carini\", \"score\": 0.7271917328355142, \"rank\": 0.37515314716380394, \"text\": \"Carini\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carini\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Carini has sinceapologised to Khelifand has said she would embrace her if she saw her again.\", \"from\": 2617, \"to\": 2709, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2617, \"end\": 2623, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carini\", \"score\": 0.7271917328355142, \"rank\": 0.37515314716380394, \"text\": \"Carini\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carini\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Khelif was one of two boxers allowed to compete in Paris despite being disqualified from the World Championships in Delhi.\", \"from\": 2711, \"to\": 2833, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2762, \"end\": 2767, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 6.465403292267622e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2827, \"end\": 2832, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Delhi\", \"score\": 0.7272205710581835, \"rank\": 0.37509861491543955, \"text\": \"Delhi\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Delhi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Delhi\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The other was Lin Yu-ting  The UN's special rapporteur on violence against women and girls has condemned the decision to allow Imane Khelif to compete in women's boxing at the Olympics, withMPsandJK Rowlingamong other critics.\", \"from\": 2834, \"to\": 3060, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2848, \"end\": 2859, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lin Yu-ting\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\"}, {\"begin\": 2865, \"end\": 2867, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Nations\", \"score\": 0.999956424797261, \"rank\": 4.311979508784281e-05, \"text\": \"UN\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Nations\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Nations\"}, {\"begin\": 2961, \"end\": 2973, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"score\": 0.9999996421621021, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Imane Khelif\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"International Olympic Committee(IOC) spokesperson Mark Adams said the two boxers fighting at the Olympics after being disqualified from last year's world championships are \\\"real people\\\" who have been competing \\\"for many years\\\" and that \\\"this is not a transgender issue\\\", the BBC reported.\", \"from\": 3062, \"to\": 3350, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3337, \"end\": 3340, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_News\", \"score\": 0.9846246488877459, \"rank\": 0.015610453280608517, \"text\": \"BBC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_News\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_News\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Differences in sex development- also known as DSD - are a group of about 40 rare conditions involving genes, hormones and reproductive organs, including genitals, that develop in the womb.\", \"from\": 3352, \"to\": 3540, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3398, \"end\": 3401, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Signals_Directorate\", \"score\": 0.9911850460161837, \"rank\": 0.008893348440711036, \"text\": \"DSD\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Signals_Directorate\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Signals_Directorate\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It means a person's sex development is different from normal.\", \"from\": 3541, \"to\": 3602, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Some people prefer to use the termintersex.\", \"from\": 3603, \"to\": 3646, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Khelif has not yet commented publicly about the controversy and despite discussions about DSD, there has been no indication to suggest that she has DSD, which is a rare condition affecting between 0.05 and 1 per cent of the population.\", \"from\": 3648, \"to\": 3883, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3738, \"end\": 3741, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Signals_Directorate\", \"score\": 0.9911850460161837, \"rank\": 0.008893348440711036, \"text\": \"DSD\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Signals_Directorate\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Signals_Directorate\"}, {\"begin\": 3796, \"end\": 3799, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Signals_Directorate\", \"score\": 0.9911850460161837, \"rank\": 0.008893348440711036, \"text\": \"DSD\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Signals_Directorate\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Signals_Directorate\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Itcan result in outwardly female individuals having male chromosomesor anatomy.\", \"from\": 3884, \"to\": 3963, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Others could have a very rare type of DSD where they have both ovarian and testicular tissue (sometimes one ovary and one testis).\", \"from\": 3965, \"to\": 4095, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4003, \"end\": 4006, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Signals_Directorate\", \"score\": 0.9911850460161837, \"rank\": 0.008893348440711036, \"text\": \"DSD\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Signals_Directorate\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Signals_Directorate\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Their genitals may appear female or male or could look different from either.\", \"from\": 4096, \"to\": 4173, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"When born, some people have a chromosome pattern other than the usual XY or XX.\", \"from\": 4175, \"to\": 4254, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4245, \"end\": 4247, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.69888863652451e-16, \"text\": \"XY\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\"}, {\"begin\": 4251, \"end\": 4253, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.007273448730328e-46, \"text\": \"XX\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They may have one X chromosome (XO), or they may have an extra chromosome (XXY).\", \"from\": 4255, \"to\": 4335, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4287, \"end\": 4289, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/OLPC_XO\", \"score\": 0.6539023302532638, \"rank\": 0.4338651381101152, \"text\": \"XO\", \"types\": [\"Q1067263\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/OLPC_XO\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/OLPC_XO\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Their internal and external sex organs can be either male or female, but they may not go through full physical development at puberty.\", \"from\": 4337, \"to\": 4471, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For example, a child with female sex organs may not start having periods.\", \"from\": 4472, \"to\": 4545, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Doctors tend to check a baby for DSD soon after birth if they are showing signs such as undescended testicles or if a baby's genitals look different.\", \"from\": 4547, \"to\": 4696, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4580, \"end\": 4583, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Signals_Directorate\", \"score\": 0.9911850460161837, \"rank\": 0.008893348440711036, \"text\": \"DSD\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Signals_Directorate\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Signals_Directorate\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tests including ultrasounds and blood tests can be done before a baby's sex is registered.\", \"from\": 4697, \"to\": 4787, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Many forms of DSD do not require any medical care other than understanding the baby's development and knowing what to expect as they grow older.\", \"from\": 4789, \"to\": 4933, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4803, \"end\": 4806, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Signals_Directorate\", \"score\": 0.9911850460161837, \"rank\": 0.008893348440711036, \"text\": \"DSD\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Signals_Directorate\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Signals_Directorate\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Other people with DSD are sometimes only diagnosed once puberty begins and it becomes clear something is not right.\", \"from\": 4935, \"to\": 5050, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4953, \"end\": 4956, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Signals_Directorate\", \"score\": 0.9911850460161837, \"rank\": 0.008893348440711036, \"text\": \"DSD\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Signals_Directorate\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Signals_Directorate\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The issue has caused a lot of people toshare their opinions on the matter.\", \"from\": 5052, \"to\": 5126, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Some commentators have said it is wrong for a person who is considered biologically as strong as a man to compete against a biological woman, as it would give an unfair advantage.\", \"from\": 5127, \"to\": 5306, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Former GB swimmer Sharron Daviessaid: \\\"This is a biological male fighting a female & absolutely everyone can see it, they have also failed gender screening, twice & have XY chromosomes.\", \"from\": 5308, \"to\": 5493, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5315, \"end\": 5317, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999823091839575, \"rank\": 1.7690904083769933e-05, \"text\": \"GB\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There is no ambiguity that the IOC do not care if a female gets seriously hurt.\", \"from\": 5494, \"to\": 5573, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5525, \"end\": 5528, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.113333803259931e-42, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Or worse.\", \"from\": 5574, \"to\": 5583, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am astonished at the weakness of the media.\\\"\", \"from\": 5584, \"to\": 5630, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A string of MPs made similar condemnations.\", \"from\": 5632, \"to\": 5675, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Anna Turley, Labour MP for Redcar, said: \\\"This is just not acceptable @Olympics - enough.\\\"\", \"from\": 5677, \"to\": 5767, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5677, \"end\": 5688, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Turley\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anna Turley\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Turley\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Turley\"}, {\"begin\": 5704, \"end\": 5710, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Redcar_Racecourse\", \"score\": 0.9878138036312176, \"rank\": 0.007320468661973672, \"text\": \"Redcar\", \"types\": [\"Q1777138\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Redcar_Racecourse\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Redcar_Racecourse\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And Labour MP Rosie Duffield said: \\\"This is not ok @iocmedia #Paris2024 Listen to women.\\\"\", \"from\": 5769, \"to\": 5858, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5789, \"end\": 5797, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Duffield\", \"score\": 0.9899144706270542, \"rank\": 0.010159209151545473, \"text\": \"Duffield\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Duffield\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Duffield\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jim Shannon, of the Democratic Unionist Party, also chimed in: \\\"How in the name of sanity is this supported by the IOC?\", \"from\": 5860, \"to\": 5979, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5860, \"end\": 5871, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jim_Shannon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jim Shannon\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jim_Shannon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jim_Shannon\"}, {\"begin\": 5880, \"end\": 5905, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Democratic_Unionist_Party\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3597233950562075e-30, \"text\": \"Democratic Unionist Party\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Democratic_Unionist_Party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Democratic_Unionist_Party\"}, {\"begin\": 5975, \"end\": 5978, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.113333803259931e-42, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When Pierre de Coubertin said 'all sports for all people' he would never have intended for men fighting women to be one of those sports.\", \"from\": 5980, \"to\": 6116, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5985, \"end\": 6004, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pierre_de_Coubertin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pierre de Coubertin\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pierre_de_Coubertin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pierre_de_Coubertin\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Male violence on females cannot be tolerated as a spectatorsport.\\\"\", \"from\": 6117, \"to\": 6183, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"On Thursday morning, Mark Adams, an IOC spokesman, said those competing in the boxing are compliant with the eligibility rules.\", \"from\": 6185, \"to\": 6312, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6206, \"end\": 6216, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_Adams_(basketball,_born_May_1956)\", \"score\": 0.5137413298826524, \"rank\": 0.45833333333321225, \"text\": \"Mark Adams\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_Adams_(basketball,_born_May_1956)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_Adams_(basketball,_born_May_1956)\"}, {\"begin\": 6221, \"end\": 6224, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.113333803259931e-42, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He said: \\\"What I'd repeat is all the competitors comply with the competition eligibility rules and that's as it should be.\", \"from\": 6314, \"to\": 6436, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That's how these boxers concerned have taken part in these Games, have taken part in previous world championships, have taken part in previous Olympic Games, have taken part in regional and continental competitions.\", \"from\": 6437, \"to\": 6652, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The IOC is saddened by the abuse that the two athletes are currently receiving.\", \"from\": 6654, \"to\": 6734, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6659, \"end\": 6662, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.113333803259931e-42, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The IBA's recognition was withdrawn by the IOC in 2023 following its suspension in 2019.\\\"\", \"from\": 6735, \"to\": 6824, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6739, \"end\": 6742, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9999998432986227, \"rank\": 1.567017860267551e-07, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}, {\"begin\": 6778, \"end\": 6781, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.113333803259931e-42, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"South African runner and Olympic gold medallist Caster Semenya has a DSD called 5-alpha-reductase deficiency, which means she has\\u00a0the male XY chromosomes and produces higher levels of testosterone than normal for women.\", \"from\": 6826, \"to\": 7045, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6874, \"end\": 6888, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caster_Semenya\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Caster Semenya\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caster_Semenya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caster_Semenya\"}, {\"begin\": 6895, \"end\": 6898, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Signals_Directorate\", \"score\": 0.9911850460161837, \"rank\": 0.008893348440711036, \"text\": \"DSD\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Signals_Directorate\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Signals_Directorate\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This DSD can occur in people with female reproductive anatomy and genitalia, as in\\u00a0Semenya's case.\", \"from\": 7047, \"to\": 7145, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7052, \"end\": 7055, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Signals_Directorate\", \"score\": 0.9911850460161837, \"rank\": 0.008893348440711036, \"text\": \"DSD\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Signals_Directorate\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Signals_Directorate\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She has previously detailed how she has internal testes and no uterus, but does have a vagina.\", \"from\": 7146, \"to\": 7240, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Semenya, who dominated women's running events between 2009 and 2019, learned at the same time as the rest of the world that she had a DSD.\", \"from\": 7242, \"to\": 7380, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7376, \"end\": 7379, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Signals_Directorate\", \"score\": 0.9911850460161837, \"rank\": 0.008893348440711036, \"text\": \"DSD\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Signals_Directorate\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Signals_Directorate\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She was forced to take drugs such as the contraceptive pill to lower her testosterone to align with new rules that limited the level of the hormone in women's events.\", \"from\": 7381, \"to\": 7547, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Fellow runners Francine Niyonsaba of Burundi, Kenya's Margaret Nyairera Wambui and\\u00a0Namibia's Christine Mboma and Beatrice Masilingi have also been ruled ineligible to compete in competitions due to DSDs.\", \"from\": 7549, \"to\": 7752, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7564, \"end\": 7582, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Francine_Niyonsaba\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Francine Niyonsaba\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Francine_Niyonsaba\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Francine_Niyonsaba\"}, {\"begin\": 7586, \"end\": 7593, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Burundi\", \"score\": 0.9999999844858395, \"rank\": 1.5514359027216248e-08, \"text\": \"Burundi\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Burundi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Burundi\"}, {\"begin\": 7595, \"end\": 7600, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"score\": 0.9999997777404379, \"rank\": 2.2225648108097317e-07, \"text\": \"Kenya\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\"}, {\"begin\": 7603, \"end\": 7627, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Margaret_Wambui\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Margaret Nyairera Wambui\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Margaret_Wambui\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Margaret_Wambui\"}, {\"begin\": 7632, \"end\": 7639, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Namibia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.594006195777391e-15, \"text\": \"Namibia\", \"types\": 